TITLE: Calling Azure Function from Excel Custom Function (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the complete Excel custom function `add` from `functions.js`. It asynchronously calls the deployed `AddTwo` Azure Function using the `fetch` API with a POST request and 'text/plain' content type (due to potential CORS issues). It sends parameters in the body, parses the JSON response, and resolves the promise with the calculated 'answer'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-add-in-samples/blob/main/Excel-custom-functions/AzureFunction/README.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function add(first, second) {
  //If you publish the Azure Function online, update the following URL to use the correct URL location.
  const url = "https://excel-custom-functions.azurewebsites.net/api/addtwo";

  return new Promise(async function (resolve, reject) {
    try {
      //Note that POST uses text/plain because custom functions runtime does not support full CORS
      const response = await fetch(url, {
        method: "POST",
        headers: {
          "Content-Type": "text/plain",
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({ first: first, second: second }),
      });
      const jsonAnswer = await response.json();
      resolve(jsonAnswer.answer);
    } catch (error) {
      console.log("error", error.message);
    }
  });
}
```

