TITLE: Querying Teams, Uploading Files, and Sending Messages with Microsoft Graph API - .NET C#
DESCRIPTION: This C# snippet shows how to interact with Microsoft Teams via the Microsoft Graph API to obtain a list of Teams and their channels, upload newly constructed spreadsheets to OneDrive associated with a Team or channel, and send a chat message with a link to the uploaded spreadsheet. The code depends on Azure Active Directory authentication and properly configured Graph API permissions. Key methods include TeamsList for querying teams, ChannelsListForTeam for channels within a team, and UploadSpreadsheet for creating, uploading, and messaging about the spreadsheet.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-add-in-samples/blob/main/Samples/excel-open-in-teams/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
// In ProductsController.cs
public async Task<IActionResult> TeamsList()
{
    var accessToken = await _graphAPIHelper.GetAccessTokenAsync();
    var teams = await _graphAPIHelper.CallGraphAPIAsync<TeamsResponse>(
        "https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/me/joinedTeams", accessToken);
    return View(teams);
}

public async Task<IActionResult> ChannelsListForTeam(string teamId)
{
    var accessToken = await _graphAPIHelper.GetAccessTokenAsync();
    var channels = await _graphAPIHelper.CallGraphAPIAsync<ChannelsResponse>(
        $"https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/teams/{teamId}/channels", accessToken);
    return View(channels);
}

public async Task<IActionResult> UploadSpreadsheet(string teamId, string channelId, SpreadsheetViewModel vm)
{
    using (var memoryStream = new MemoryStream())
    {
        var builder = new SpreadsheetBuilder();
        builder.CreateSpreadsheet(memoryStream, vm.Headers, vm.DataRows);
        memoryStream.Position = 0;
        var accessToken = await _graphAPIHelper.GetAccessTokenAsync();
        var uploadResult = await _graphAPIHelper.UploadFileToChannel(
            teamId, channelId, "productdata.xlsx", memoryStream, accessToken);
        var chatMessage = await _graphAPIHelper.SendChannelMessageWithFileLink(
            teamId, channelId, uploadResult.WebUrl, accessToken);
        return View("UploadToTeams", new { RedirectUrl = chatMessage.MessageLink });
    }
}
```

