TITLE: Implementing Code Splitting with Dynamic Import in React (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows a React component `App` implementing code splitting. It uses the dynamic `import()` syntax within an event handler (`handleClick`) to load `moduleA.js` asynchronously when a button is clicked, improving initial load time. It uses a Promise chain (`.then`, `.catch`) to handle the loaded module.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-add-in-samples/blob/main/Samples/Office.ASP.NETCoreReactAddins/excel-js/ClientApp/README.md#_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import React, { Component } from 'react';

class App extends Component {
  handleClick = () => {
    import('./moduleA')
      .then(({ moduleA }) => {
        // Use moduleA
      })
      .catch(err => {
        // Handle failure
      });
  };

  render() {
    return (
      <div>
        <button onClick={this.handleClick}>Load</button>
      </div>
    );
  }
}

export default App;
```

