TITLE: Writing 'Hello World!' to Worksheet - Office.js Excel - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a function that, when called (e.g. by a button), writes 'Hello world!' to cell A1 on the currently active worksheet using the Office JS Excel API. Requires Office.js and Excel runtime environment. The key parameter is the context object, which provides access to the workbook and enables committing changes via context.sync(). The function returns a promise; errors should be caught and handled as per best practices.
