TITLE: Using Office JS API to Insert Paragraph in Word (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript function, intended to be called from Blazor C# via interop, demonstrates interacting with a Word document using the Office JS API. It utilizes `Word.run` to create an execution context, inserts a new paragraph at the beginning of the document body using `context.document.body.insertParagraph`, and finally calls `context.sync()` to execute the queued commands. This function is exported so it can be imported and called from C#.
