TITLE: Initializing JavaScript Interop in Blazor Component (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This C# code snippet, typically placed within a Blazor component's code-behind file (.razor.cs), runs after the component has rendered for the first time. It uses the JSRuntime service to asynchronously import a corresponding JavaScript module (e.g., './Pages/Index.razor.js') and stores a reference to it (JSModule) for later interop calls.
