TITLE: Writing to Outlook Email Message Body with Office.js in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This function writes 'Hello world!' to the body of a new Outlook email message using the Office.js API. It calls Office.context.mailbox.item.body.setAsync() with HTML coercion, and provides a callback that checks operation success and writes an error message if needed. Prerequisites include Office.js APIs available via Office Add-in context in Outlook.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-add-in-samples/blob/main/Samples/hello-world/outlook-hello-world/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
/**
 * Writes 'Hello world!' to a new message body.
 */
function sayHello() {
  Office.context.mailbox.item.body.setAsync(
    'Hello world!',
    {
      coercionType: 'html', // Write text as HTML
    },

    // Callback method to check that setAsync succeeded
    function (asyncResult) {
      if (asyncResult.status == Office.AsyncResultStatus.Failed) {
        write(asyncResult.error.message);
      }
    }
  );
}
```

