TITLE: Scheduling Batch Request Execution in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet, part of the `_pushOperation` function, demonstrates how a remote request is scheduled. It uses `setTimeout` to delay the execution of `_makeRemoteRequest` by 100 milliseconds, allowing multiple operations to be batched together if they occur in quick succession. A flag `_isBatchedRequestScheduled` prevents multiple timeouts from being set simultaneously.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-add-in-samples/blob/main/Excel-custom-functions/Batching/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// If a remote request hasn't been scheduled yet,
// schedule it after a certain timeout, e.g. 100 ms.
if (!_isBatchedRequestScheduled) {
  _isBatchedRequestScheduled = true;
  setTimeout(_makeRemoteRequest, 100);
}
```

