TITLE: Configuring WebSocket Proxy in package.json (JavaScript/JSON)
DESCRIPTION: Example configuration within the `proxy` object in `package.json` specifically for proxying WebSocket connections (e.g., for Socket.io or native WebSockets). It requires setting the `target` to the compatible WebSocket server URL (prefixed with `ws://` or `wss://`) and explicitly enabling WebSocket proxying by setting `ws: true`. This allows the development server to handle WebSocket upgrade requests correctly.
