TITLE: Extending Office.TableData: Appending Rows from Array (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet defines an extension method `addRange` for the `Office.TableData` object. It appends rows to the table data based on an input array of objects. It iterates through the provided array and, for each object, creates a new row containing only the values corresponding to the headers already defined in the `TableData` object's `headers[0]` array. This method supports multiple appends, useful for paged data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/officedev/office-add-in-samples/blob/main/Samples/Excel.JsonToOfficeTable/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
//extension to Office.TableData to add a range of rows
Office.TableData.prototype.addRange = function (array) {
    for (i = 0; i < array.length; i++) {
        var itemsTemp = new Array();
        $(this.headers[0]).each(function (ii, ee) {
            itemsTemp.push(array[i][ee]);
        });
        this.rows.push(itemsTemp);
    }
}
```

